eting, compliance, licensing, vendor partnerships, and local marketing—aligning local execution with BrewDog's international brand strategy.\n- Maintained a consistent labor cost of 17% on average through low staff turnover, training, smart flexible scheduling & consistent staff motivation.", "experiences/0/jobLocation": "Bangkok, Bangkok City, Thailand", "experiences/0/jobStartedOn": "7-2024", "experiences/0/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/0/title": "General Manager", "experiences/1/companyName": "Burger & Lobster Siam Paragon", "experiences/1/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/1/jobDescription": "Franchise Outlet owned by JCK Hospitality PCL\n\n• Delivers revenues and profits by developing, marketing, financing, providing great restaurant service and managing a multicultural team\n• To support and maintain Brand awareness within the Territory’s local market\n• Devise a restaurant business plan by surveying restaurant demand; conferring with people in the community; identifying and evaluating competitors, preparing financial, marketing, and sales projections. Carry out adequate research to enable an aspirational but realistic business plan to be devised and implemented.\n• Responsibility for meeting the restaurants financial objectives, preparing strategic and annual forecasts and budgets, establishing and monitoring financial controls, developing and implementing strategies to increase average spending per person.\n• Understand and interpret financial data and P&L information to enable business decisions and appropriate actions to be taken in a timely manner.\n• Control purchases and inventory; negotiating prices and contracts with local suppliers;\n• Maintain operations by following brand policies and standard operating procedures;\n• Responsibility for all areas of human resources including recruiting, selecting, orienting, training, assigning, scheduling, coaching, disciplining and management of staff; communicating job expectations; planning, monitoring, appraising; motivating and inspiring.\n• Take appropriate steps to mitigate all potential risks, which may include but is not limited to training and development of all staff and setting clear expectations in these areas.\n• Maintains safe, secure, and healthy environment by establishing, following, and enforcing sanitation standards and procedures; complying with health and legal regulations;\n• To work collaboratively with the UK Marketing team and other relevant departments.\n• To monitor, investigate and resolve complaints concerning food quality and service standards", "experiences/1/jobEndedOn": "5-2025", "experiences/1/jobLocation": "Bangkok, Bangkok City, Thailand", "experiences/1/jobStartedOn": "11-2022", "experiences/1/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/1/title": "General Manager", "experiences/2/companyName": "Burger & Lobster Siam Paragon", "experiences/2/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/2/jobDescription": "Overlooking the pre opening of Burger & Lobster's second outlet in Bangkok located at Siam Paragon Mall. \n- Hiring & training of all Front of House & Back of House staff from scratch \n- Ensuring all brand standards are complied from construction to handover\n- Work out allocated budget for all opening needs \n- Liaising with the brand & franchise owner on all real time construction progress, marketing needs & working closely on the timeline. \n- Work closely with B&L's director of business development, executive brand development chef & brand operations manager on food & beverage menu development. \n- Sourcing of necessary suppliers for all aspects of restaurant opening.", "experiences/2/jobEndedOn": "11-2022", "experiences/2/jobLocation": "Bangkok, Bangkok City, Thailand", "experiences/2/jobStartedOn": "6-2022", "experiences/2/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/2/title": "General Manager (Pre-Opening)", "experiences/3/companyName": "Burger & Lobster Singapore", "experiences/3/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/3/jobDescription": "- Devised the post covid reopening business plan by enabling events & business strategies to boost revenue. \n- Restructuring & readapting to new business needs for the post covid era as borders reopened. \n\nAchievements: \n- Single handedly secured two lucrative wedding contracts to be held at the restaurant premises. (beating other luxury hotels & restaurants options) \n- Implemented wedding manuals & wedding event SOPs, managed customer relations with the wedding couples and ensuring that their desired wedding comes to life. \n- Personalized multiple course western menus together with the brand executive development chef based on the wedding clients' preferences and not straying away from the essence of the brand. \n- Handled all pre wedding preparations from contracts to menu planning & headed the wedding day operations smoothly.", "experiences/3/jobEndedOn": "6-2022", "experiences/3/jobLocation": "Burger & Lobster Raffles Hotel, Singapore", "experiences/3/jobStartedOn": "1-2022", "experiences/3/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/3/title": "Assistant General Manager", "experiences/4/companyName": "Burger & Lobster Singapore", "experiences/4/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/4/jobDescription": "- Assisting the General Manager in the day to day restaurant operations as well as financial\naspects of Burger & Lobster at Ra􀁂es Hotel Singapore.\n- In charge of launching and securing events (MICE, Birthdays, Weddings) being organized & held\nat the main dining area & outdoor terrace seating area.\n- Designed & published an Events Deck / Pamphlet for the restaurant.\n- In charge of individual corporate home deliveries for big clienteles such as DBS Bank, OCBC\nBank, Bank of China, AIA & medical companies (multiple locations as many as 130 locations)\nduring the Covid-19 pandemic.\n- Training & Development of rank & file staff as well as junior management staff.\n- In charge of maintaining, handling, troubleshooting & updating the restaurant's main POS\nsystem (ICG).\n- Upselling the restaurant space for weddings, dealing directly with the clients, planning &\nexecuting the entire wedding procedure.\n- Implementing and executing the full delivery business module in light of Covid-19 pandemic\ndine-in restrictions & lockdowns.\n- Constantly coming up with business ideas & promotions to sustain the business during the\nCovid-19 Pandemic lockdowns.\n\n***************************************************************************\n\n\nAchievements:\nSecured bulk corporate delivery sales for 2021 - Burger & Lobster Raffes Hotel\n- Amassed up to $60,000++ in corporate sales (only for delivery) for 2021 (bulk & individual locations up to 130 at a given time) as corporate events were restricted due to Covid-19. Handled the entire process from enquiries to logistics & execution to ensure all orders were delivered in a good & timely manner all over Singapore.", "experiences/4/jobEndedOn": "12-2021", "experiences/4/jobLocation": "Burger & Lobster Raffles Hotel, Singapore", "experiences/4/jobStartedOn": "10-2019", "experiences/4/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/4/title": "Assistant Manager", "experiences/5/companyId": "940129", "experiences/5/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/5/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/grand-hyatt-singapore/", "experiences/5/companyName": "Grand Hyatt Singapore", "experiences/5/companySize": "501-1000", "experiences/5/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:940129", "experiences/5/companyWebsite": "https://www.hyatt.com/grand-hyatt/en-US/sinrs-grand-hyatt-singapore", "experiences/5/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/5/jobDescription": "- Managing & running 3 floors of Events Space catering to big MICE events, weddings, VIP\nmeetings & off-site catering as well\n- Running and ensuring the event smoothness of many big name clients such as Prudential, Van\nCleef & Arpels, Singapore Airlines, Hermes & many more while maintaining Hyatt International\nbrand standards\n- Overall in charge for the hotel's Mid-Autumn Festival 2019\n- Managing and controlling all expenses to maximize GOP\n- Ensuring compliance and hygiene standards are met constantly\n- Managing up to 120 staff at certain periods depending on business volumes\n- Overall in charge of beverages for the hotel's Events Department\n- Rolling out new beverage menu & packages to increase beverage revenue\n\n*****************************************************************************\n\nAchievements: \nIncreased overall Sales & Profit for the Mid-Autumn Festival 2019 - Grand Hyatt\nSingapore\n- Achieved SGD$1,000,000 in sales during Grand Hyatt Singapore's Mid-Autumn Festival 2019. This record sales is the\nfirst time ever that Grand Hyatt Singapore has hit the million dollar mark for a Mid-Autumn Festival Campaign. Also\nachieved a 2% higher GOP than the previous year which also meant setting a new record high.", "experiences/5/jobEndedOn": "10-2019", "experiences/5/jobLocation": "Singapore", "experiences/5/jobLocationCountry": "SG", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "10-2018", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/5/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQGysGvfznphQQ/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1705640713955/grand_hyatt_singapore_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=KwaWK81x6SLQfSOKdYZ_fLmKUWk-XlxMFrRL3SxVsgk", "experiences/5/title": "Assistant Manager - Event Service", "experiences/6/companyId": "940129", "experiences/6/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/6/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/grand-hyatt-singapore/", "experiences/6/companyName": "Grand Hyatt Singapore", "experiences/6/companySize": "501-1000", "experiences/6/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:940129", "experiences/6/companyWebsite": "https://www.hyatt.com/grand-hyatt/en-US/sinrs-grand-hyatt-singapore", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "mezza9 delivers the world’s best cuisines through nine different dining experiences, including:\n • ​grill: 