ven better than what I had asked for. He always had the initiative to start projects and was very proactive. He was great with clients and with following up on anything he was assigned to do. I would recommend or rehire him anytime.", "recommendations/0/name": "David N.", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Hospitality Development | 10 + years | Project Managing | Construction | Interior design | Hotel / F&B / Event Management Background", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nilsson-david/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAQqw6QBHKmsT0tJWAKyEdXbDpLQinsUxE8", "recommendations/1/context": "Eric managed Nora directly", "recommendations/1/date": "February 6, 2024", "recommendations/1/description": "Nora worked with me as our resort manager at the Six Senses Con Dao. She was always willing to help and was well-organized.", "recommendations/1/name": "Nora Feranecz", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Cluster Hotel Manager at Millennium Hotels", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nora-feranecz-54284228/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAXRtIIB29a_9NycXj0va_5BYR17zLzkJLg", "recommendations/2/date": "February 6, 2024", "recommendations/2/description": "Sophie worked with me as a trainee at the Rembrandt Hotel in Bangkok in various capacities. She was a quick learner with a very good attitude. She kept growing professionally. We therefore decided to hire her back after graduation. I hope to have the pleasure of working with her again.", "recommendations/2/name": "Sophie Dinh", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Event Specialist | Project Coordinator | Luxury Wedding Planner | Event & Hospitality Specialist", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sophiedinhthi/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB7wZ3UB5isWZob2zQLAdjysa5WMseEQ_JY", "recommendations/3/context": "Eric was Alan's client", "recommendations/3/date": "November 15, 2019", "recommendations/3/description": "I worked with Alan for some ten years as GM of an associate hotel of the Warwick Hotels and Resorts and as such was often in contact with him in regards to electronic distribution and digital marketing. Alan is both professional and well informed of the quickly changing digital landscape. He understands the business from a hoteliers perspective.\nHe helped us on numerous occasions and am pleased to recommend him.", "recommendations/3/name": "Alan Gonzalez", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Hospitality Digital Distribution Leader | Direct Booking Strategy | CRS • GDS • OTA Ecosystems | HSMAI Revenue Management Executive of the Year", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alan-gonzalez-0361711/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAzmeoBK3jQCbq9mLAjFVrP-5_s01RVHQc", "recommendations/4/context": "Eric worked with Jason on the same team", "recommendations/4/date": "January 20, 2019", "recommendations/4/description": "Jason Roe served as a Director and Treasurer at Skal International Bangkok 2016-2018 whilst I was the President. Jason was not only an excellent Treasurer but also contributed greatly to the board by introducing many web-based procedures to facilitate administration of the Club. Jason was a very active board member who voiced his opinions, supported the Club and was an asset to us all.", "recommendations/4/name": "Jason Roe", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Branch Manager at West Capital Lending | Wholesale Rates | Access to 180+ Lenders | Educate • Guide • Empower", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/yourratebroker/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAmeC8IBB950tg2vV9SdVhC9Cl2TsJw4ioA", "recommendations/5/context": "Eric was Romain's client", "recommendations/5/date": "March 8, 2018", "recommendations/5/description": "I met Romain when we contacted Warwick International hotels back in 2008 and he was our contact point during our negotiations.\nHe has since rejoined the Warwick Hotels and Resorts and is our contact. Romain has helped us with various aspects of our relationship including giving us good advice on electronic distribution and other marketing aspects.\nRomain is easy to work with and is good at finding solutions to problems.", "recommendations/5/name": "Romain Bernard", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Deputy Director of Business Development – International Partnerships B2B Partnerships | Luxury, Retail & Tourism", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rbernardparis/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIdqFUBHGYkQ1MTiYuBhcjgpMxnZrSAnZE", "recommendations/6/context": "Eric managed Bernd Otto directly", "recommendations/6/date": "February 21, 2017", "recommendations/6/description": "Bernd was an incredible e-commerce and e-marketing man. I wish he would have stayed longer as I have seldom come across someone as knowledgeable and proactive e-marketing person. He increased our visibility a lot, which translated into sales. I would love to have him back.", "recommendations/6/name": "Bernd Otto Grahl", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Group Digital Manager @ Gondwana Collection Namibia | Hotel Management, E-Marketing", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/berndottograhl/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAU49LUBme7eU-LnhzFf1YpzKtxImSgj8Rs", "recommendations/7/context": "Eric was Kevin's client", "recommendations/7/date": "February 21, 2017", "recommendations/7/description": "I met Kevin in 2011. We had been using a competing channel-manager and booking engine. He convinced my colleagues and I to buy the Siteminder channel manager, being more versatile and efficient, as well as their booking-engine solution. \nI have always found Kevin easy to work with and open to suggestions on product improvement in the early days, before both products were as good as they are today. It has always been a pleasure to work with Kevin as he not only sold us the products, but was able to constantly support us until now.\"", "recommendations/7/name": "Kevin Tatem", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Regional Head - APAC", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kevintatem/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAC2JW8BZS3AkS0f-_txq19zSHVfkVmzshU", "recommendations/8/context": "Eric managed Wayne directly", "recommendations/8/date": "April 2, 2012", "recommendations/8/description": "I worked with Wayne in Phuket, Maldives and Samui. I can strongly recommend Wayne as a very capable manager. He is well rounded and has many strengths. He is both detail oriented as well as a people's person. He is an excellent marketeer especially in new media. He is on top of numbers, yields and profitability. he constantly seeks improvement both of services as well as bottom line. Wayne is someone who always looks for the positive as well as ways to improve. As mentioned above would recommend him to any interested employer and would always be happy to rehire Wayne as a manager.", "recommendations/8/name": "Wayne Lunt", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Studying at Notre Dame, Fremantle", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/wayne-lunt-3139758/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGRBn8Bh4oWw3lmj_3HiCo_eSB61xv8SyU", "recommendations/9/context": "Eric worked with Andrew but they were at different companies", "recommendations/9/date": "April 1, 2012", "recommendations/9/description": "I have worked with Andrew over the last few years. It is always a pleasure dealing with him as he is a thorough professional and a gentleman. I look forward to continue to do business with him in whatever capacity he is in.", "recommendations/9/name": "Andrew Morgan", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Hotel consultancy | Sales & Marketing | XML & API connectivity / Product & Purchasing Management / Tour Operating", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewmorgan82/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAApq76IBXmzdkECC8U6guGQFCuCaKNb5MUY", "recommendations/10/context": "Eric was Rob's client", "recommendations/10/date": "April 29, 2011", "recommendations/10/description": "A fantastic rep\nA pleasure to work with, well connected, personable, creative and always positive.\nHe has in a short time span helped us increase our UK business considerably\nGreat follow up and highly recommend him to other hotels/ chains looking for UK representation", "recommendations/10/name": "Rob Haynes", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Director/Owner, Red Tree Representation", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rob-haynes-a43b667/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAFqyFMB_YPr1_gNNbHbrsj74BGwBa4k7RY", "recommendations/11/context": "Eric worked with Paul but they were at different companies", "recommendations/11/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/11/description": "I have had the pleasure, over the years, to both see Paul at work as well as having had this develop into a friendship. \nHe is a true gentleman and an industry leader that people look up to. He has an easy charm with enormous energy. He easily sees business possibilities and is yet someone very easy to work with. He keeps looking for win-win situation for both clients and suppliers which of course makes beautiful business sense.\nI would recommend clients and suppliers alsike to work with Paul.", "recommendations/11/name": "Paul Humphreys FRSA FRGS", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Chairman & C.E.O. at dmEARTH Group of Companies / dmAFRICA / dmASIA / luxEARTH / Destination Professionals", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/phumphreys/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEh7KwB70TqFsLiTpMB_Ck_DH91zxh3mH8", "recommendations/12/context": "Eric managed Phil directly", "recommendations/12/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/12/description": "Phil joined me for a fourth time, this time in Europe for the opening of the first resort for Six Senses in Europe.\nHe moved to Spain to assist me in both the project as well as technical services until we were able to establish an opening team. I once again appreciated his eye for detail, organisational skills as well as intellect. He is both an operational asset as well as a pleasure to have around.", "recommendations/12/name": "Phil Nunan", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "(Luxury) Hospitality Project Person.", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/phil-nunan-5978225/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEC4sMBpG24oq7vHiw-P_aSRkZzV7ykyLU", "recommendations/13/context": "Eric managed Phil directly", "recommendations/13/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/13/description": "Phil spent his last Internship with me as Management Trainee in Phuket, Thailand. He successfully assisted me as an aid to GM doing several projects\nPhil is a very intelligent and quick worker\nI later employed Phil as Assistant F&B Manager at White Sands, Maldives. This was a challenging but rewarding assignment where we had to reposition the island and the resort. We turned the resort around from a loss making resort to one of the best performing islands in a very short time span. Phil was again instrumental in assisting us to do so.\nWe worked together again at the Six Senses. He was assigned to assist us in opening our (Six Senses) first hotel in Europe. The Six Senses Latitude in Jafre, Catalonia, Spain.\nPhil is a very conscientious person with a keen eye to detail. He is highly organised and used to work with Critical Paths timelines. In addition Phil is also a pleasure to have around, possessing a well developed sense of humour and a tremendous intellect.", "recommendations/13/name": "Phil Nunan", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "(Luxury) Hospitality Project Person.", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/phil-nunan-5978225/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEC4sMBpG24oq7vHiw-P_aSRkZzV7ykyLU", "recommendations/14/context": "Eric was Phil's teacher", "recommendations/14/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/14/description": "Phil spent his last Internship with us as Management Trainee. He successfully assisted me as aid to GM doing several projects\nPhil is a very intelligent and quick worker", "recommendations/14/name": "Phil Nunan", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "(Luxury) Hospitality Project Person.", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/phil-nunan-5978225/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEC4sMBpG24oq7vHiw-P_aSRkZzV7ykyLU", "recommendations/15/context": "Eric was Stephen's client", "recommendations/15/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/15/description": "I have worked with Stephen a E-TravelBlacboard and now at Global Travel Media\nHe is not only a very good and conscientious journalist/editor but also someone who really understands the travel industry and it's challenges \nHe is someone who constantly thinks out of the box looking for new opportunities and possibilities not only for himself but also others\nAs an advertiser with his new venture I can also say that we have had some excellent feedback resulting in real bookings at a very reasonable conversion rate", "recommendations/15/name": "Stephen Morton", "recommendations/15/subtitle": "Founder EGTMedia.com", "recommendations/15/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephenjmorton/", "recommendations/15/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGSn3wBvBKGCBQ2IlyC_D8K9ACo0V58g5g", "recommendations/16/context": "Eric worked with Nassima but on different teams", "recommendations/16/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/16/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Nassima in three different capacities during my tenure at Six Senses 2004-2008.\nShe was always very professional with a keen eye for detail\nShe is a very strong candidate for operational jobs of any kind", "recommendations/16/name": "Nassima Leipold", "recommendations/16/subtitle": "Managing Director at Heimstaden FM Service Solutions GmbH", "recommendations/16/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nassima-leipold-b275425/", "recommendations/16/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD4I88BKIy9jV9bWIDNE5MGFUA2UT7gfH8", "recommendations/17/context": "Eric was Dave's client", "recommendations/17/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/17/description": "David helped me teach English and business skills at the Six Senses Hideaway in Koh Samui 2005-2008\nWe were very satisfied with his courses and the teachers that he privided us during this time", "recommendations/17/name": "Dave Belcher", "recommendations/17/subtitle": "Founder at Total Quality Hotel Management", "recommendations/17/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dave-belcher/", "recommendations/17/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAOthMIBJ4GhiR2T9ZeWJfl-Vg9JENxNoiU", "recommendations/18/context": "Addie was Eric's client", "recommendations/18/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/18/description": "I have had the pleasure working with Addie in many various capacities over a thirty year time-span.\nShe has always been highly professional since I first met her. She is also a person with the ability to think out of the box. She is today a doyen within the Thai travel industry because she has taken such an ethic and professional route and has an amazing ability to also cover small details as well as she does the big picture.\nIt is always a pleasure to work with her.", "recommendations/18/name": "Addie Hirunkate", "recommendations/18/subtitle": "Non Executive Director : Asia Concierge", "recommendations/18/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/addie-hirunkate-7267798/", "recommendations/18/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGJi84BPqro-u0qac0F8dZ-OoFiKf7186U", "recommendations/19/context": "Eric worked with Henric but they were at different companies", "recommendations/19/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/19/description": "Henric and I go back many decades of interaction since our college days.\nHe is often involved in projects where I also know many of the parties involved are people who are close to. Henric is full of charm and is also a very knowledgeable person especially in the Air Communication industry. Henric always conducts his business in a very proffesional way and always pays great attention to detail and has good follow up skills. A highly intelligent and preoffessional person that I would not hesitate in recommending", "recommendations/19/name": "Henric Nauckhoff", "recommendations/19/subtitle": "CCO & Partner, ePiece Ltd.", "recommendations/19/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/henricnauckhoff/", "recommendations/19/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGJwNkBNGEhkvBKP0SrH8OWGsA90LNa0Uw", "recommendations/20/context": "Eric worked with Kay but on different teams", "recommendations/20/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/20/description": "I worked with Kay when she was DOSM at Westin Shanghai\nWe would often interact and Kay always carried out her duties in a very proffesional way and had great attention to detail and good follow up skills. A highly intelligent and preoffessional person\nWe have since had our paths cross many times, including in her present capacity", "recommendations/20/name": "Kay FILL", "recommendations/20/subtitle": "Hospitality Sales & Marketing Support", "recommendations/20/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kay-fill-9b459b8/", "recommendations/20/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGCpNgBw9VTqwyB5u62fPez9LWurI0359Q", "recommendations/21/context": "Eric was Michael Paul's client", "recommendations/21/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/21/description": "I worked with Michael when he was a partner in providing my opening team with Transformational Thinking 2004/2005\nIt proved an effective tool in transforming many hosts who had had little hospitality experience into a fantastic team that later with this and much other training were good enough to make us win Conde Nast's Best Hotel in The World award 2008 and Best of the Best!!!", "recommendations/21/name": "Michael Paul Stephens", "recommendations/21/subtitle": "Passionate Learning and Development Professional", "recommendations/21/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-paul-stephens/", "recommendations/21/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHy6CkBB4sJBm5PLeVwzOtq8TaX2_5TVgY", "recommendations/22/context": "Eric worked with Barry on the same team", "recommendations/22/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendations/22/description": "I worked with Barry Arnold for more than a couple of years\nHe was an inspiration in all that he engaged himself whether it was rethinking F&B concepts, hotel concepts in both strategy, design and marketing\nBarry is one of those highly gifted people who's brain just keep storming up new ideas and even if out of the box are very feasible and doable\nHe is a true inspiration to work with\nHe is just a superb light designer apart from an author, play wright and so many other gifts.\nI wish I would have many more opportunities to work with him.", "recommendations/22/name": "Barry Arnold", "recommendations/22/subtitle": "Managing Director BAA", "recommendations/22/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/barryarnold/", "recommendations/22/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALcb78BY6tqoBxep6hVF_gJTZ5BZ9bNzKw", "recommendations/23/context": "Eric worked with Greg on the same team", "recommendations/23/date": "April 27, 2010", "recommendations/23/description": "I know Greg since many years and have interacted with Greg in various capacities. However, joining the opening of Sila Evason Hideawaay or Six Senses Hideaway, Koh Samui (as it became known as) I had the pleasure to work with Greg as the Director of Sales & Marketing of Six Senses Resorts. He was material to working with us on planning strategies that laid the ground work for our resort rising to take the number one slot on Samui island in both average room rate as well as in REVPAR and we managed to show a healthy GOP in our first year of operation. He is a very good strategic and out of the box thinker. His biggest strengths being more in the marketing and sales strategies than sales. Saying that he also helped to effectively sell the hotel rooms. He was very popular with all our sales and PR offices worldwide as well as being very close with many of our key partners.\nI even today  consult with him on many key marketing strategies.", "recommendations/23/name": "Greg Seddon", "recommendations/23/subtitle": "Director at Epikurean Hotels & Lifestyle", "recommendations/23/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/greg-seddon-6a29b820/", "recommendations/23/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAARrYNoBpBRWdqjJzaIx-fsh14VKeb0QcDA", "recommendations/24/context": "Eric managed Thomas J. directly", "recommendations/24/date": "April 10, 2010", "recommendations/24/description": "I would re-employ Thomas Jakobi anytime.\nHe is a chef with a passion for cooking; he is not an office chef or a chef with F&B aspirations.\nSaying that he is a very able pre-opening Chef\nI first worked with him at Six Senses Hideaway, Koh Samui, Thailand 2004-2008 and then for the opening of Six Senses Latitude, Jafre, Spain 2007-2008 (which he assisted with since 2007 even though he did not physically stay there until mid-2008)\nHis cooking was superb. Both of our two restaurants had guests raving about our food. We received several awards and many were due to the high quality of our food. Here I would like to mention the Conde Nast (UK) Readers Award 2008 as Best of the Best, Best in the World.\nHis wine knowledge is equally good and he often knows better than many wine-makers in what food would show off a wine better than another. This is partly due to being born into a family that have been wine-makers for generations.\nHe was also instrumental in assisting me together with our sommeliers in selecting an amazing wine cellar with wines not sitting in the cellar but moving all the time. A big part this was due to Thomas Jakobi ability to choose matching wines.\nHe would be working with his brigade on a daily basis to make sure high quality was met all the time. Even though he was a tough task master he quickly gained the respect of his entire brigade.\nHe was also able to consistently keep food costs under control, as well as to be on top of his budgeting. He was always a very good team player with the management. Even if he sometimes would instinctively say no he would very quickly change and find a way that would make it possible.\nHe was always interested to try new ideas and cooking methods. He always looked for the best available raw products. A better chef to work with is difficult to find.\nIn our quest to open Six Senses Lattitude, Jafre, Spain he was a key player, with a lot of openings behind him, that would work tirelessly help to work out concepts and then putting into reality. He was also able to attract some very dedicated staff.\nAs I started, I will end. I would re-employ Thomas Jakobi anytime. He is a great chef that is still growing and has an enormous passion for food.", "recommendations/24/name": "Thomas J. Jakobi", "recommendations/24/subtitle": "Executive Chef at Conrad Marina Bay Singapore", "recommendations/24/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomas-j-jakobi-567b7012/", "recommendations/24/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKp3h8BJvVSxlUMg_pEANp7OQZGhLHZFZo", "recommendations/25/context": "Eric managed Karen directly", "recommendations/25/date": "November 29, 2009", "recommendations/25/description": "My experience with Karen Millar as a Spa Manager was very good. I had called Karen back from Australia to manage the Nakalay Spa at Thavorn Beach village. This was a beautiful spa and was one of Phuket's first luxury spas. Karen had first joined us from Amanpuri and had completed a contract with us in another management position. I knew she was going to do very well managing our spa and she did.\nShe did a very good job in driving the spa to better profits by implementing a new menu as well as managing & training both therapists and consultants. At the same time she marketed the spa not only to in-house guests but also managed to build up a large visiting clientele. She worked proactively and I can recommend Karen for the job she did for me as Spa Manager and I hope to have the pleasure to work with her again.", "recommendations/25/name": "Karen Millar", "recommendations/25/subtitle": "Owner, Spa Consulting Australasia", "recommendations/25/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/karen-millar-1b34018/", "recommendations/25/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF7t9cB3mHYwcW8YGn8O-dwC0N2HlQkkFs", "recommendations/26/context": "Eric was Lisa's client", "recommendations/26/date": "April 16, 2009", "recommendations/26/description": "Lisa is passionate about people, systems (control of processes) and positive reinforcement of systematic change which she is able to convey with ease.\nShe has a knack of breaking down perceived problems and re-focus people on what really should be the mission, based on Core Values and Company Culture. She also focuses on the customer (whether internal or external) and does so by encouraging the team to achieve this as well as to manage expectations.", "recommendations/26/name": "Lisa Ekström", "recommendations/26/subtitle": "Owner/CEO at Kamoja AB", "recommendations/26/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/lisaekstrom/", "recommendations/26/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEn_t8Be3Mw_BCVxURuZO5uzvTZ86z6SHE", "recommendations/27/context": "Eric managed Andreas directly", "recommendations/27/date": "September 29, 2008", "recommendations/27/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Andreas Kraemer both at the White sands Resort & Spa, Maldives as well as had him join me at the Six Senses Hideaway at Samui. He not only rose in short time to be the Resort Manager, but continued to act as Acting General Manager when I was transferred to Spain, for the last seven months.\nAndreas is a pleasure to work with, he is a born hotelier who is well organised as well as being proactive in achieving results.He was in no small way instrumental in us winning Conde Nast Readers award 2008 as \"The best hotel in the world\".\nI can wholeheartedly recommend him and would be very happy to work with him again if the opportunity presented itself.", "recommendations/27/name": "Andreas Kraemer", "recommendations/27/subtitle": "General Manager | Luxury Hotelier | Multi-Property & Brand Repositioning Leader | Guest Experience Lead | Asset Growth Expert | Advocate of Sense of Place | Trusted by UHNW Guests & Owners", "recommendations/27/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreaskraemerak/", "recommendations/27/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADj1bcBdc4bao96hQj5-B_Hlc0prro3avY", "recommendations/28/context": "Eric worked with John but they were at different companies", "recommendations/28/date": "July 4, 2008", "recommendations/28/description": "I have known John for more than 20 years. We have often had guests & customers in common as well as often cooperated in various ways. I have always found John to be a true professional striving to maintain high standards. At the same time, he runs a very tight ship and always ran very profitable hotels.", "recommendations/28/name": "John Girard", "recommendations/28/subtitle": "50+ Years Hotel Industry Professional Across Five Continents", "recommendations/28/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/johnalexandergirard/", "recommendations/28/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEdwO0BfA5UZ_2W0o7Iu3GVpHc7jJamopI", "recommendations/29/context": "Eric worked with Andres but they were at different companies", "recommendations/29/date": "June 17, 2008", "recommendations/29/description": "I know Andres professionally for many years, especially during his tenure at Imperial Hotel Samui. We were both active as Vice Presidents in THA (Thai Hotel Association) South-East Chapter. Andres was always pro-active working hard both for his company as well as for the betterment of the island and the industry. He was always well liked by his peers as well as his employees. He is also an accomplished linguist, speaking many languages. I can only say that I highly recommend Andres as a professional as well as a good person.", "recommendations/29/name": "Andres Rubio", "recommendations/29/subtitle": "VP Planing at Asiatique Hotels & Resorts", "recommendations/29/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andres-rubio-94077a8/", "recommendations/29/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGJk8AB64j91PjkcpCFlhyJTZTquCdeGjE", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Viktor worked with Eric but they were at different companies", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "December 17, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "in all my years in the travel business have I never seen a GM more visible then Eric, he is the ultimate host.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Viktor Weyand", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Founder at Viktor Incentives & Meeting", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/viktor-weyand-7019b18/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGSMbEB8hOm5Gl-_Jy8dBgLDRRY3UpRGB8", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Göran worked with Eric but they were at different companies", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "January 28, 2012", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Eric is a well organized and structured person with the availability to \"make things happen\". Friendly and very much an expert in interact with others.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Göran Nyhlen", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Managing Director at Scandinavian Deli", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/göran-nyhlen-babaa36/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAE6nPMBzFx_Oi_SB6U7M5uF7QrK8uu5lTw", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Andreas reported directly to Eric", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "May 31, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "Eric has been my mentor since day one. I had the opportunity of working for Eric both in the Maldives and on Koh Samui. \nIn both properties we won many awards and the worlds most prestigious hospitality award we achieved with the Six Senses Hideaway on Koh Samui, always thanks to the team and the exceptional leadership of Eric.His unique close-to-guest-and-to-staff leadership is what makes him spearhead the industry in the luxury segment. I haven't met many I would title a \"True Hotelier\"and it would be a pleasure to be part of his team again at any time. He's a visionary personality and a true host with a very complex network of people, from all over the world and it's a tremendous delight to meet within these circles. Thank you Eric for making hospitality even more special!", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Andreas Kraemer", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "General Manager | Luxury Hotelier | Multi-Property & Brand Repositioning Leader | Guest Experience Lead | Asset Growth Expert | Advocate of Sense of Place | Trusted by UHNW Guests & Owners", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreaskraemerak/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADj1bcBdc4bao96hQj5-B_Hlc0prro3avY", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Dave reported directly to Eric", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "August 30, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Eric for two or three years at Six Senses.\nIt was a valuable lesson watching not only a consummate professional in hospitality management operate and run a hotel, but what struck me most was Eric's obvious passion for the business and his genuine desire to lead, encourage and develop the people he managed.\n\nHe is a genuinely expert manager, a knowledgeable professional and a good mentor.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Dave Belcher", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Founder at Total Quality Hotel Management", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dave-belcher/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAOthMIBJ4GhiR2T9ZeWJfl-Vg9JENxNoiU", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Henric worked with Eric but on different teams", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "August 23, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Eric and I go back to high-school days and we have enjoyed a friendship, both private and professional, uninterrupted since then. I know of very few people who have as much charm combined with an inquisitive nature that has resulted in an individual who can manage any relationship, professional or private, with absolute panache. Eric and I have worked together on projects that I have been involved in and has impressed both me and my colleagues with his great attention to detail, his sense for the situation at hand and his ability to cut through complex information in order to make it seem simple. I strongly recommend Eric as a professional and as a friend!", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Henric Nauckhoff", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "CCO & Partner, ePiece Ltd.", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/henricnauckhoff/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGJwNkBNGEhkvBKP0SrH8OWGsA90LNa0Uw", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Paul was Eric's client", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "August 22, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "A true professional hotelier. Always a pleasure to stay in a hotel managed by Eric. From the moment you enter the door, his style of management, care level for the guests and staff alike, and superb attention to detail is evident throughout every facet of the organisation. One of the last of the true \"Gentleman Hoteliers\" and a great ambassador for the luxury hospitality industry.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Paul Humphreys FRSA FRGS", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Chairman & C.E.O. at dmEARTH Group of Companies / dmAFRICA / dmASIA / luxEARTH / Destination Professionals", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/phumphreys/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEh7KwB70TqFsLiTpMB_Ck_DH91zxh3mH8", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Kenneth was Eric's client", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "November 3, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "Met Eric as his hotel was next to the condo I resided in on the Ping River in Chiang Mai, Thailand.  You only allow us to choose 3 attributes to express the qualities of this fine gentleman who speaks more languages than I can remember, has savoir-faire and is a genuine omnipotent host. He masterminded my 50th birthday celebration at the Westin and it was truly one of the high points in my life for which I never shall forget.", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "Kenneth Moskowitz", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "Sr Commercial Associate at The Keyes Company", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kenmoskowitzrealtor/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGJvnYBbYClxTo9mm6j1VeLdy9CDni6Q8U", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Karen reported directly to Eric", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "July 7, 2008", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "Eric mentored me into the Spa industry but more importantly he was the calm and well organized leader and teacher through my first and second experiences of Crises Management.  He also taught me quite a few tricks on revenue and profit (for which I am now renowned for), negotiating, patience and people management. These are lessons I am sure he has forgotten he taught me (as he would have taught many others along the way) but I remember always. Eric is a true inspiration and great teacher to all under his employ.", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Karen Millar", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "Owner, Spa Consulting Australasia", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/karen-millar-1b34018/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAF7t9cB3mHYwcW8YGn8O-dwC0N2HlQkkFs", "ski